==English==
===Etymology===
Originally named ''Antlia pneumatica'' (air pump) in the 18th century by the [[French]] [[astronomer]] Nicolas Louis de Lacaille. From {{L.}} ''[[antlia]]'' a [[pump]] for [[draw]]ing water; {{Gr.}} [[άντλία]]

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia|Antlia}}
'''Antlia'''

#{{constellation}}: A faint [[winter]] [[constellation]] of the [[northern]] sky, said to resemble a [[pump]]. The common English name is Air pump.

